1
00:00:20,791 --> 00:00:23,375
I can't claim to know
exactly what's happening.

2
00:00:23,458 --> 00:00:27,250
But a situation such as this one
troubles me to say the least.

3
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:31,208
[MAKAROV] Hm. And the first
sign was them not answering

4
00:00:31,291 --> 00:00:32,833
when you called?

5
00:00:32,916 --> 00:00:34,041
[LUCY]
Yeah.

6
00:00:35,375 --> 00:00:37,250
[YUKINO] A contract
between a celestial wizard

7
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:40,625
and their spirit is an
unbreakable, sacred bond.

8
00:00:40,708 --> 00:00:44,458
So this sort of thing shouldn't
happen. It's unheard of.

9
00:00:44,541 --> 00:00:48,791
I'm afraid this means something
extremely serious is going on.

10
00:00:48,875 --> 00:00:50,916
With them ignoring you
and trying to hurt Lucy,

11
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:53,916
something major's gone down,
but what could it be?

12
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,666
I got no idea.
But when I see Loke again,

13
00:00:57,750 --> 00:01:00,416
I'm gonna beat some
manners into him!

14
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,916
Why don't you take us back
to the beginning, Lucy.

15
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:05,791
Maybe we can figure out
where things went wrong.

16
00:01:05,875 --> 00:01:06,958
[LUCY grunts]

17
00:02:39,083 --> 00:02:41,125
[MAKAROV]
They want total freedom?

18
00:02:41,208 --> 00:02:43,541
But you have such a good
relationship with them.

19
00:02:43,625 --> 00:02:45,041
Loke's like the head honcho

20
00:02:45,125 --> 00:02:47,291
of all the zodiac
spirits, isn't he?

21
00:02:47,375 --> 00:02:49,250
Maybe he's just being
super rude and trying

22
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:50,875
to stir up some kind of trouble.

23
00:02:50,958 --> 00:02:53,208
Exactly, that's why we
should go with my plan

24
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:54,791
and beat the snot
outta that jerk!

25
00:02:54,875 --> 00:02:57,041
Beating someone up
isn't a plan, you idiot.

26
00:02:57,125 --> 00:02:58,750
Well at least I
thought of something!

27
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:00,166
How are you gonna fix it?

28
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:01,333
Shut up.

29
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:08,416
I fear it's more than
defiance. It's a revolt.

30
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:11,041
But why would it just
happen so suddenly?

31
00:03:11,125 --> 00:03:14,541
That's not it. I refuse
to believe they'd do that.

32
00:03:14,625 --> 00:03:17,541
Yes, I don't want to
either. But still...

33
00:03:17,625 --> 00:03:21,166
I know. I'll call
Grandpa Crux again!

34
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:22,583
[HAPPY] But when you
summoned him earlier,

35
00:03:22,666 --> 00:03:25,291
Virgo beat him and then
forced his gate to close.

36
00:03:25,375 --> 00:03:26,958
[LUCY]
I know he'll find a way.

37
00:03:27,041 --> 00:03:27,916
Open.

38
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,875
Gate of the Southern Cross!

39
00:03:29,958 --> 00:03:31,458
Crux!

40
00:03:33,541 --> 00:03:35,125
[LUCY]
Wait. What?

41
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:37,208
I summoned Crux, not you!

42
00:03:37,291 --> 00:03:39,625
[HOROLOGIUM] "Coming here
is extremely dangerous,

43
00:03:39,708 --> 00:03:42,958
so I had this gentleman
bring me." He says,

44
00:03:43,041 --> 00:03:44,791
through continuous snoring.

45
00:03:44,875 --> 00:03:46,750
Well, the others may have
roughed him up a bit,

46
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:48,666
but at least he
gets to sleep it off!

47
00:03:50,875 --> 00:03:52,333
[HAPPY]
Library Panic

48
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:56,250
We're back!

49
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:57,958
Please tell me
the kitchen's open.

50
00:03:58,041 --> 00:04:00,958
I could definitely use a
bite to eat after that gig.

51
00:04:01,041 --> 00:04:01,750
[JET]
Uh...

52
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:02,833
[DROY]
Hello?

53
00:04:02,916 --> 00:04:04,958
[LEVY]
Is something wrong, you guys?

54
00:04:05,041 --> 00:04:06,208
Shh!

55
00:04:06,291 --> 00:04:07,791
[LUCY]
Grandpa Crux.

56
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:10,000
Can you please tell us what's
going on in the celestial world?

57
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:12,708
[CRUX] At first, everything
was so peaceful. And then,

58
00:04:12,791 --> 00:04:16,000
all of a sudden, rebellion
began to spread like wildfire.

59
00:04:16,083 --> 00:04:18,875
Contracts between Zodiac
spirits and their key holders

60
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:21,916
became null and void.
There was no warning for this,

61
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,791
much less any kind
of reason given.

62
00:04:26,791 --> 00:04:28,833
[CRUX] They've been
running amok ever since.

63
00:04:28,916 --> 00:04:30,625
Destroying the celestial world,

64
00:04:30,708 --> 00:04:35,625
and sending us silver keys into
hiding, fearful for our lives.

65
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:37,625
Well what about
old mustache face?

66
00:04:37,708 --> 00:04:40,583
Can't the Celestial Spirit King
restore order somehow?

67
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:43,625
[CRUX] Perhaps he could,
if anyone knew where he was.

68
00:04:43,708 --> 00:04:46,000
He's disappeared without
any kind of trace.

69
00:04:46,083 --> 00:04:49,291
You mean you haven't even
seen him since? That's bad.

70
00:04:49,375 --> 00:04:51,291
Leo the Lion is
the official leader

71
00:04:51,375 --> 00:04:53,291
of the Zodiac spirits,
so we can assume

72
00:04:53,375 --> 00:04:55,041
they're acting
under his command.

73
00:04:55,125 --> 00:04:56,666
And he had the nerve
to pretend like

74
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:58,416
he didn't even know who we were!

75
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,083
The only thing he
wanted to talk about

76
00:05:00,166 --> 00:05:02,833
was how they were tryin'
to get "total freedom."

77
00:05:02,916 --> 00:05:04,291
[CRUX]
Liberam.

78
00:05:04,375 --> 00:05:05,666
What does that mean?

79
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:07,250
[YUKINO]
I brought this with me.

80
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:10,041
I had a feeling this book had
something to do with all this.

81
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:11,208
[HAPPY]
What is it?

82
00:05:11,291 --> 00:05:12,833
Would you mind if I take a look?

83
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:13,750
Please.

84
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:15,333
Now, let me see here.

85
00:05:15,416 --> 00:05:18,833
This seems to be a magic book
written in ancient Meridisian.

86
00:05:18,916 --> 00:05:22,041
Quite a few entries on
"Liberam."Reading through this,

87
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:25,208
I think it's more like
an encyclopedia instead.

88
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:26,958
We can always count on you.

89
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:28,333
Let me ask you something.

90
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:30,625
How did you know to
find this specific book?

91
00:05:30,708 --> 00:05:32,958
[YUKINO] Well, I did a little
research on my own,

92
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:34,625
and came across this title.

93
00:05:34,708 --> 00:05:36,833
But that's about
as far as I got.

94
00:05:36,916 --> 00:05:39,666
I thought someone here could
help me find out more.

95
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:42,916
[CRUX] I must admit, I wasn't
aware that such ancient writings

96
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,000
still existed in
the human world.

97
00:05:45,083 --> 00:05:47,625
But I can tell you that
the word 'Liberam' refers

98
00:05:47,708 --> 00:05:50,875
to a certain ritual the
celestial spirits can perform.

99
00:05:50,958 --> 00:05:52,125
It's a ritual?

100
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:54,208
What all do you know about it?

101
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:55,458
[CRUX]
Hm.

102
00:05:55,541 --> 00:05:57,750
All I know is speculation.
But the story goes

103
00:05:57,833 --> 00:06:01,208
that a spirit can obtain
this freedom Leo spoke of

104
00:06:01,291 --> 00:06:03,000
by performing the Liberam.

105
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:04,875
This part looks
important you guys.

106
00:06:04,958 --> 00:06:08,333
It says here that "The Liberam
requires a celestial globe

107
00:06:08,416 --> 00:06:11,166
to free the spirits
from their chains."

108
00:06:11,250 --> 00:06:12,916
From their chains?

109
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,791
Is that really how
they feel about it?

110
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,541
It can't be.
They're our friends.

111
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:20,541
[NATSU] I guarantee pouting
about it won't solve anything.

112
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:22,666
[HAPPY] Yeah, you're just gonna
give yourself frown lines

113
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,166
if you keep that up.

114
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:25,500
[LUCY sighs]

115
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:27,791
[NATSU] I'm the only one
with a real plan here.

116
00:06:27,875 --> 00:06:31,291
And that's kickin' Loke's
butt till he's back to normal.

117
00:06:31,375 --> 00:06:33,916
At least you care. Thank you.

118
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:37,041
This celestial globe
that the ritual requires.

119
00:06:37,125 --> 00:06:38,958
Do you know where
it can be found?

120
00:06:39,041 --> 00:06:41,833
[CRUX] I'm afraid I do not.
Hopefully, it's not already

121
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:44,375
in the hands of those
rebellious spirits.

122
00:06:44,458 --> 00:06:46,041
That could be tragic.

123
00:06:46,125 --> 00:06:49,041
It seems like we would know
if it was in their possession.

124
00:06:49,125 --> 00:06:50,541
Aye sir.

125
00:06:50,625 --> 00:06:53,333
[DROY] If they had it, I don't
think that they would have

126
00:06:53,416 --> 00:06:55,083
revealed themselves to Lucy.

127
00:06:55,166 --> 00:06:56,541
Yeah, they probably
would've already

128
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:58,208
started the ritual by now.

129
00:06:58,291 --> 00:07:00,875
That is a valid point.
There's no reason for them

130
00:07:00,958 --> 00:07:02,958
to show up if they're
really independent.

131
00:07:03,041 --> 00:07:04,958
[ERZA] Have you been able
to find much information

132
00:07:05,041 --> 00:07:07,708
on the Liberam in there, Levy?

133
00:07:07,791 --> 00:07:11,458
Actually, there are pages
and pages of stuff on it.

134
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:13,333
But the ink is way
too old and faded

135
00:07:13,416 --> 00:07:15,333
to tell what most
of it even says.

136
00:07:15,416 --> 00:07:17,250
[ERZA] I wonder if we
can find another book

137
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:19,458
that can tell us more about it.

138
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:20,500
Wait a sec.

139
00:07:20,583 --> 00:07:22,125
I have an idea.

140
00:07:22,208 --> 00:07:23,333
[LEVY]
Yeah!

141
00:07:23,416 --> 00:07:24,791
We should check out
the Library of Sorcery

142
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:27,583
to see if we can
find something there!

143
00:07:27,666 --> 00:07:32,000
Hm. Perhaps we may even
discover that these bizarre

144
00:07:32,083 --> 00:07:34,291
weather phenomena
we've been experiencing,

145
00:07:34,375 --> 00:07:36,791
and the disruption in the
spirit world are related.

146
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:38,125
But we need evidence.

147
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:40,041
[ERZA]
I volunteer.

148
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:42,000
We need as much
reliable intelligence

149
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:43,708
on the subject as
we can possibly

150
00:07:43,791 --> 00:07:45,500
get our hands on, and quickly.

151
00:07:45,583 --> 00:07:47,625
And then we can make our move.

152
00:07:47,708 --> 00:07:49,541
I trust you can
handle that, Erza?

153
00:07:49,625 --> 00:07:52,500
[ERZA] Right! We'll
split into teams of two.

154
00:07:52,583 --> 00:07:55,916
[ERZA] Cana and I, Wendy
and Carla, Gray and Juvia,

155
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,791
Gajeel and Lily,
and Mira and Elfman.

156
00:07:58,875 --> 00:08:00,750
If we spread out we
can cast a wide net

157
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,291
for any relevant information.

158
00:08:02,375 --> 00:08:04,791
Once Warren returns,
we can use his telepathy

159
00:08:04,875 --> 00:08:07,083
to relay what've found
amongst the teams.

160
00:08:07,166 --> 00:08:10,291
[ERZA] Lucy, Natsu,
Yukino, Levy, and Happy will

161
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:12,916
head to the Library of Sorcery.

162
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,041
Aye, Sir!

163
00:08:14,125 --> 00:08:15,541
I love being a bookworm!

164
00:08:15,625 --> 00:08:17,333
Are you fired up, Natsu?

165
00:08:17,416 --> 00:08:18,916
Hey!

166
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,166
[LEVY]
He's gone!

167
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,375
[HAPPY] So are the clock
and the sleepy old man.

168
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:23,916
No. He didn't!

169
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,541
That nitwit will
be the death of me!

170
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:32,250
[NATSU]
Hey listen. Thanks for the help!

171
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:33,625
You guys rule!

172
00:08:33,708 --> 00:08:35,833
[HOROLOGIUM] "I'm more than
happy to be of service.

173
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:38,208
But I can't say that it's
very intelligent of you

174
00:08:38,291 --> 00:08:40,416
to go against the
redhead's orders like this"

175
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,583
He grumbles disparagingly.

176
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:45,041
[NATSU] If you know me, you
know that I don't let anybody

177
00:08:45,125 --> 00:08:47,666
get away with hurting
Lucy's feelings!

178
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:50,083
[HOROLOGIUM] "I admire your
loyalty, but information should

179
00:08:50,166 --> 00:08:53,333
always come before action."
He advises contrarily.

180
00:08:53,416 --> 00:08:55,375
Well, it's too
late for that now!

181
00:08:58,750 --> 00:09:01,875
[NATSU growls]

182
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,666
[NATSU]
Alright, ya bunch of star jerks,

183
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:05,708
you've got some
'splainin' to do!

184
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:12,750
Whoa! You two should find
somewhere safe to hide.

185
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:14,791
[CRUX] We will,
but please be careful!

186
00:09:16,291 --> 00:09:19,666
[TAURUS] Welcome to the
celestial spirit world, mortal.

187
00:09:19,750 --> 00:09:21,750
[NATSU]
Taurus? What's with you?

188
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:24,541
I thought you were supposed
to be all wacky and pervy.

189
00:09:24,625 --> 00:09:25,958
[TAURUS]
Then you would be wrong.

190
00:09:26,041 --> 00:09:30,541
I may have once behaved
so boorishly, but no more.

191
00:09:30,625 --> 00:09:32,208
[NATSU groans]

192
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:36,375
[TAURUS] I pride myself
on gentlemanly manners.

193
00:09:36,458 --> 00:09:38,083
Even as I destroy you.

194
00:09:38,166 --> 00:09:39,791
Is that so?

195
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,916
I'm gettin' kinda
worried about Natsu.

196
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,666
Don't forget that
time works differently

197
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:54,416
in the celestial world, so even
though it's been a while,

198
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:56,875
he's probably just
now arriving there.

199
00:09:56,958 --> 00:09:58,416
Yeah, good point.

200
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:00,000
We're all a little worried.

201
00:10:00,083 --> 00:10:02,166
But our team needs to
focus on finding clues

202
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:03,916
to help us stop the Liberam.

203
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,541
[HAPPY] There's gotta
be something promising

204
00:10:05,625 --> 00:10:07,250
in all these stacks of books.

205
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:10,041
Have you guys found
anything that looks useful?

206
00:10:10,125 --> 00:10:11,916
[LEVY] Not yet.
And we are gonna need

207
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,291
every single book on
that list I gave you.

208
00:10:14,375 --> 00:10:15,750
[HAPPY]
Aye, Sir!

209
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:17,166
[LUCY]
Listen to this.

210
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:19,208
"There are stories
from long ago that tell

211
00:10:19,291 --> 00:10:21,541
of the Liberam ritual
being performed.

212
00:10:21,625 --> 00:10:23,666
But they're just legends,
and cannot be verified."

213
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:25,750
[LEVY] "The name
'Meridies' means 'south'

214
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:29,125
in the Meridisian language."
Duh, I know that already!

215
00:10:29,208 --> 00:10:31,375
[YUKINO] According to this:
"The Liberam can only

216
00:10:31,458 --> 00:10:34,250
be performed in a
specific location.

217
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:36,750
Known as the Astral Spiritus."

218
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:38,958
[LUCY] Does it happen
to say where that is?

219
00:10:39,041 --> 00:10:40,333
Can we go there?

220
00:10:40,416 --> 00:10:42,750
[YUKINO] It only says
what it is, not where it is.

221
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:45,416
Maybe there's an atlas
in here that can tell us.

222
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:46,666
[LUCY]
What about you?

223
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,833
Finding any info on
the celestial globe?

224
00:10:48,916 --> 00:10:50,291
[LEVY]
No such luck.

225
00:10:50,375 --> 00:10:52,750
And all these books are
worn and faded out, too.

226
00:10:52,833 --> 00:10:55,875
But it's gotta be in
one of these old things.

227
00:10:55,958 --> 00:10:57,083
[BOTH gasp]

228
00:10:57,166 --> 00:10:58,583
[YUKINO]
What's happening?

229
00:10:58,666 --> 00:11:00,625
[LUCY] Unfortunately. I think
I recognize this feeling.

230
00:11:00,708 --> 00:11:01,625
[ALL gasp]

231
00:11:01,708 --> 00:11:02,583
[LUCY]
Uh- oh!

232
00:11:02,666 --> 00:11:05,583
[ALL scream]

233
00:11:05,666 --> 00:11:08,041
[HAPPY]
Huh? What the heck was that?

234
00:11:09,916 --> 00:11:11,166
Man, that hurts.

235
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:13,125
[YUKINO]
Are you doing okay, Levy?

236
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:17,458
Yeah. I guess so.
That was a major fall.

237
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:19,708
What do you think caused it?

238
00:11:19,791 --> 00:11:21,208
What, do you see something?

239
00:11:21,291 --> 00:11:23,625
Keep your guard up, everybody!

240
00:11:23,708 --> 00:11:24,750
[ALL scream]

241
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,333
[LUCY]
It's you.

242
00:11:28,416 --> 00:11:30,958
As soon as I felt that rumbling
I was sure you were behind it!

243
00:11:31,041 --> 00:11:32,375
[LUCY]
